content.description: Near vertical, mossy rock. Poor rock quality down low, yields to better holds up high. Walk off to the left.
content.protection: 7 bolts to a 2 bolt anchor (no rings)
content.location: 70 ft up the hill from Mission Impossible. Start climbing by crossing the bottom of a right facing corner.

content.description: Good rock for the Pinnacles and well protected, too!  Rappel 135' with double ropes to the start.
content.protection: Fourteen bolts to a three bolt anchor.

content.description:
This 120 foot route shares a start with

Mission Impossible

.  Start with a 10 foot high, right-facing corner/flake to a shared first bolt.  Mission Impossible veers up and right after this bolt.  For Get Smart, continue straight up past three bolts on lower-angle rock to the base of a steep water streak.  Climb the streak past 11 more bolts and a slot for a 3½ inch piece (the slot is between the thirteenth and fourteenth bolts; skipping the gear results in a runout that is manageable but uncharacteristic of the rest of the route).  Finish at a two-bolt anchor on lower-angle rock to the left.  Rappel or lower off.
content.protection: 15 draws, 70m rope. Anchor has mussy hooks for lowering, route has SS bolts, one 1/2" and the rest 3/8".
content.location:
See

Mission Impossible

(right), shares a first bolt.
